<h1 id="azure-vnet">Azure VNet</h1>

<h4 id="research-summary">Research Summary</h4>

<p>Azure Virtual Networks are easy to deploy, however considerations on Network Design should be thoroughly planned beforehand.</p>

<p>Creating Virtual Switches using Hyper-V Manager is also possible.</p>

<p>VMs are able to have restricted access from the public network and only gain access through a gateway VM.</p>

<p>Vnets can be interconnected using Peering.</p>
